#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.19:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Rahogatavagga"
msgstr "2. In Private"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Pañcakaṅgasutta"
msgstr "19. With Pañcakaṅga"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.19:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pañcakaṅgo thapati yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho "
"pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the master builder Pañcakaṅga went up to Venerable Udāyī, bowed, sat "
"down to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.2"
msgid "“kati nu kho, bhante udāyi, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, how many feelings has the Buddha spoken of?”"

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.3"
msgid "“Tisso kho, thapati, vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "“Master builder, the Buddha has spoken of three feelings:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr "pleasant, painful, and neutral."

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.5"
msgid "imā kho, thapati, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha has spoken of these three feelings.”"

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.7"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "“Sir, Udāyī, the Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings."

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.8"
msgid "Dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "He’s spoken of two feelings:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr "pleasant and painful."

msgctxt "sn36.19:1.10"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā, santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā "
"bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha said that neutral feeling is included as a peaceful and subtle "
"kind of pleasure.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.224"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.19:2.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, Udāyī said to him:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.2"
msgid "“na kho, thapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings,"

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.3"
msgid "Tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "he’s spoken of three.”"

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.5"
msgid "imā tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.7"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings,"

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.8"
msgid "Dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "he’s spoken of two.”"

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:2.10"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā, santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā "
"bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.19:3.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, Udāyī said to him:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.2"
msgid "“na kho, thapati, dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of two feelings,"

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.3"
msgid "Tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "he’s spoken of three.”"

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.4"
msgid "Sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.5"
msgid "imā tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.6"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time, Pañcakaṅga said to Udāyī:"

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.7"
msgid "“na kho, bhante udāyi, tisso vedanā vuttā bhagavatā."
msgstr "“The Buddha hasn’t spoken of three feelings,"

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.8"
msgid "Dve vedanā vuttā bhagavatā—"
msgstr "he’s spoken of two.”"

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.9"
msgid "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.10"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ, bhante, adukkhamasukhā vedanā, santasmiṃ esā paṇīte sukhe vuttā "
"bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.11"
msgid ""
"Neva sakkhi āyasmā udāyī pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ saññāpetuṃ, na panāsakkhi "
"pañcakaṅgo thapati āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ saññāpetuṃ."
msgstr "But neither was able to persuade the other."

msgctxt "sn36.19:3.12"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena thapatinā saddhiṃ "
"imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Udāyī and Pañcakaṅga."

# abhivadevta is in the parallel passage at MN 59, obviously is elided here.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.19:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi."
msgstr "Then he went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "sn36.19:4.2"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako āyasmato udāyissa pañcakaṅgena "
"thapatinā saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi."
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.225"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.19:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Santameva, ānanda, pariyāyaṃ pañcakaṅgo thapati udāyissa bhikkhuno "
"nābbhanumodi;"
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, the explanation by the mendicant Udāyī, which the carpenter "
"Pañcakaṅga didn’t agree with, was quite correct."

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.2"
msgid ""
"santañca panānanda, pariyāyaṃ udāyī bhikkhu pañcakaṅgassa thapatino "
"nābbhanumodi."
msgstr ""
"But the explanation by Pañcakaṅga, which Udāyī didn’t agree with, was also "
"quite correct."

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.3"
msgid "Dvepi mayā, ānanda, vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""
"In one explanation I’ve spoken of two feelings. In another explanation I’ve "
"spoken of three feelings, or five, six, eighteen, thirty-six, or a hundred "
"and eight feelings."

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.4"
msgid "Tissopi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.5"
msgid "Pañcapi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.6"
msgid "Chapi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhārasāpi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.8"
msgid "Chattiṃsāpi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.9"
msgid "Aṭṭhasatampi mayā vedanā vuttā pariyāyena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.10"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo."
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways."

#. VAR: viharissantīti → viharissanti (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn36.19:5.11"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ "
"sulapitaṃ, na samanumaññissanti, na samanujānissanti, na samanumodissanti, "
"tesaṃ etaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ "
"mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharissantīti."
msgstr ""
"This being so, you can expect that those who don’t concede, approve, or "
"agree with what has been well spoken will argue, quarrel, and fight, "
"continually wounding each other with barbed words."

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.12"
msgid "Evaṃ pariyāyadesito kho, ānanda, mayā dhammo."
msgstr "I’ve explained the teaching in all these different ways."

msgctxt "sn36.19:5.13"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ pariyāyadesite kho, ānanda, mayā dhamme ye aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ "
"sulapitaṃ samanumaññissanti samanujānissanti samanumodissanti, tesaṃ etaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ "
"piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharissantīti."
msgstr ""
"This being so, you can expect that those who do concede, approve, or agree "
"with what has been well spoken will live in harmony, appreciating each "
"other, without quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each "
"other with kindly eyes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.19:6.1"
msgid "Pañcime, ānanda, kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.3"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing. …"

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.4"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.5"
msgid "Ime kho, ānanda, pañca kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.6"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, ānanda, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual "
"stimulation is called sensual pleasure."

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.7"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati kāmasukhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.8"
msgid "Ye kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "There are those who would say"

# Following PTS reading sattā for santam, although I am not certain of this.
msgctxt "sn36.19:6.9"
msgid "‘etapparamaṃ santaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings "
"experience."

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.10"
msgid "idaṃ nesāhaṃ nānujānāmi."
msgstr "But I don’t acknowledge that."

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.11"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn36.19:6.12"
msgid "Atthānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "Because there is another pleasure that is finer than that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.226"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.19:7.1"
msgid ""
"Katamañcānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca?"
msgstr "And what is that pleasure?"

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ "
"savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.3"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, etamhā sukhā aññaṃ sukhaṃ abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr "This is a pleasure that is finer than that."

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.4"
msgid "Ye kho, ānanda, evaṃ vadeyyuṃ:"
msgstr "There are those who would say"

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.5"
msgid "‘etapparamaṃ santaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"that this is the highest pleasure and happiness that sentient beings "
"experience."

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.6"
msgid "idaṃ nesāhaṃ nānujānāmi."
msgstr "But I don’t acknowledge that."

msgctxt "sn36.19:7.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

